Class InputPlugin

java.lang.Object
  ca.mcgill.hs.plugin.InputPlugin

Direct Known Subclasses:
BluetoothLogger, GPSLogger, GSMLogger, SensorLogger, WifiLogger
public abstract class InputPlugin
extends java.lang.Object
implements Plugin

Abstract class to be extended by all InputPlugins. Provides an interface for using InputPlugins.

Method Detail

getPreferences

public static android.preference.Preference[] getPreferences(android.preference.PreferenceActivity activity)
This method returns an array of Preference objects for the given InputPlugin. By default, this method returns null. If a specific InputPlugin wants to define Preferences, they must override this method.

Parameters:
activity - The PreferenceActivity in which the preferences will appear
Returns:
an array of the Preferences of this object.

hasPreferences

public static boolean hasPreferences()
Returns whether or not this InputPlugin has Preferences. By default, this method returns false. If a given InputPlugin overrides the getPreferences(Context) method, they must also override this method to let it return true.

Returns:
whether or not this InputPlugin has preferences.

onPluginStart

protected abstract void onPluginStart()
Called when this InputPlugin is started. This method is meant to be overridden.

onPluginStop

protected abstract void onPluginStop()
Called when this InputPlugin is stopped. This method is meant to be overridden.

onPreferenceChanged

public void onPreferenceChanged()
Signals the plugin that preferences have changed. InputPlugin objects with preferences should override this method if something changes at runtime when preferences change. If this method is not overridden in a new plugin implementation, the preferences for that plugin will only update the next time the service is started.
